'''[[debit]] [[card]]'''
# A card much like a [[credit card]], instead taking money directly from the [[bank account]] rather than borowing money at a rate of [[interest]], which works almost exactly like a credit card using the same protocol, but also has an alternate function called the "debit" function that uses a PIN instead of a signature, and is signified by a logo on the back of the card instead of the front (i.e., Plus, Interlink, Star vs. Visa, Mastercard, American Express, or Discover).